<h2>Maryland Incentives & Rebates</h2>

<p>Maryland offers a comprehensive suite of incentives that significantly improve the economics of solar panel and HVAC installations. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit on the total installed cost of solar systems through 2032, with the credit stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. This credit applies to the full system cost including equipment, installation, permits, and interconnection fees, making it one of the most valuable incentives available to Maryland homeowners.</p>

<p>At the state level, Maryland provides solar grants up to \$1,000 for residential installations through the Maryland Energy Administration, helping to further reduce upfront costs. The state also offers property tax exemptions for solar installations, meaning the added value from solar panels won't increase property tax assessments. Additionally, Maryland's Renewable Energy Portfolio Standard creates a market for Solar Renewable Energy Certificates (SRECs), allowing solar system owners to earn additional income by selling certificates representing their clean energy production.</p>

<p>BGE and other Maryland utilities offer various rebate programs for high-efficiency HVAC equipment, typically providing \$300-800 rebates for heat pumps and air conditioning systems that meet specific efficiency criteria. BGE's Smart Energy Savers Program offers additional incentives for comprehensive home energy improvements, including bonus rebates when customers combine multiple upgrades like HVAC systems and insulation improvements. The utility also provides time-of-use rates that can enhance savings for customers with solar panels and efficient HVAC systems.</p>

<p>For geothermal heat pump installations, Maryland residents can access the federal 30% tax credit, the same incentive available for solar installations, making geothermal systems significantly more affordable. Some local jurisdictions also offer additional rebates or expedited permitting for renewable energy and high-efficiency HVAC installations, further streamlining the installation process and reducing total project costs.</p>

